## Why

While [fpm][] is great, for me, it is a bummer that it depends on `ruby`, `tar`
and other software.

I wanted something that could be used as a binary and/or as a library and that
was really simple.

So I created nFPM: a simpler, 0-dependency, as-little-assumptions-as-possible alternative to fpm.

## Getting started

Install [nfpm](https://pypi.org/project/nfpm/) using your favorite tool. For example using [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/):

```sh
uv add --dev nfpm
```

You will then have the command `nfpm` (or `nfpm.exe` on Windows) available in your PATH.

```py
import subprocess
subprocess.run(['nfpm', '--help'], check=True)
```

You can then check the documentation of the nfpm command:

- [Getting Started](https://nfpm.goreleaser.com)
- [Usage](https://nfpm.goreleaser.com/usage/)
- [Configuration reference](https://nfpm.goreleaser.com/configuration/)

